# React Rules (extends 00-core.mdc)

## Component Architecture
- Vite-based React app, not a full-stack framework.
- Keep render logic pure. Side effects in hooks or dedicated adapters.
- One component per file when reused or exceeds 80 lines.

## State Management
- Local state first (`useState`, `useReducer`). Lift only when distant components share data.
- Shared state libraries (Zustand, Redux) only when prop drilling is unmanageable — record in `docs/decisions.md`.

## Data & Side Effects
- API calls in `lib/` or feature data modules — never inline in presentation components.
- Extract custom hooks when logic repeats in 2+ components. Name descriptively (`useOrderStatus`).

## Quality
- Run `npm run lint && npm run typecheck && npm run test && npm run build` after changes.
- Use code review checklist in `AGENTS.md` §7 before submitting.


